<exercise checkit-seed="0009" checkit-slug="PS1" checkit-title="Power series">
    <statement>
        <p>
            Consider a function <m>p(x)</m> defined by <me>p(x):=\sum_{n=0}^\infty \frac{2 \, {\left(2 \, n - 1\right)}}{\left(2 \, n\right)!}x^n.</me>
            <ol>
                <li>Find <m>p_{ 2 }(x)</m>, the degree <m>2</m> polynomial approximation for <m>p(x)</m>.</li>
                <li>Use <m>p_{ 2 }(x)</m> to estimate <m>p(3)</m> by computing <m>p_{ 2 }(3)</m>.</li>
                <li>Use <m>p_{ 2 }(x)</m> to estimate <m>\displaystyle \int_{ 0 }^{ 5 }p(x)dx</m> by computing <m>\displaystyle \int_{ 0 }^{ 5 }p_{ 2 }(x)dx</m>.</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
        
    </statement>
    <answer>
            <ol>
                <li> <m> p_{ 2 }(x)=\frac{1}{4} \, x^{2} + x - 2</m>.</li>
                <li><m>p_{ 2 }(3) = \frac{13}{4}</m>.</li>
                <li><m> \displaystyle \int_{ 0 }^{ 5 }p_{ 2 }(x)dx = \frac{155}{12}</m>.</li>
            </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
